# has an elective on libcap-ng maybe?
# smartctl is a C++ program and links with /usr/lib{,64}/libstdc++...
# therefore, no longer installing to /sbin/ instead of /usr/sbin/

# Should probably run from rootfs, but smartd links with libstdc++

with info    last 20130320
with version stable 6.1 6.0
with base    gcc-g++ init-functions
with elect   libcap-ng
#with also    --sbindir=/usr/sbin
with role    disk utility
with trait   console
with info    home http://smartmontools.sourceforge.net
with source  stable $SOURCEFORGE_URL smartmontools/smartmontools/$VERSION/smartmontools-$VERSION.tar.gz
with info    cite 'hard drive monitoring and testing utility toolset
smartmontools contains two utility programs
(smartctl and smartd) to control and monitor storage
systems using the Self-Monitoring, Analysis and Reporting
Technology System (S.M.A.R.T.) built into most modern ATA
and SCSI hard disks.
It is derived from the smartsuite package,
and includes support for ATA/ATAPI-5 disks.'
